README for PyFTGL

Release 0.1a (October 21, 2007)


Introduction
------------

FTGL is a free, open source library to enable developers to use 
arbitrary fonts in their OpenGL applications. Unlike other OpenGL 
font libraries FTGL uses standard font file formats and the Freetype 
font library to open and 'decode' the fonts. It then takes that 
output and stores it in a format most efficient for OpenGL rendering.

PyFTGL turn wrap the functionality of FTGL into a Python module so 
that it can be used in conjunction with PyOpenGL.


Build Instructions
------------------

0. Prerequisites

   Make sure you have the necessary libraries before building PyFTGL.

   * FTGL
     http://homepages.paradise.net.nz/henryj/code/#FTGL

   * Freetype
     http://www.freetype.org/

   * boost::python
     http://www.boost.org/


1. Build the module.

     $ python setup.py build

2. Install the module.

     $ python setup.py install
